title: PRODUCT SHOT - EL LAING
creator: Savier Rolan B. Moya
description: El Pork Laing is one of the all-time favorite cuisines in the Bicol region. This recipe made by Masiram by L’s is unique as the ingredients include dried taro leaves, pork, coconut oil, chilies, and a secret condiment to add flavor and deliver its original taste. These taro leaves are being cooked in coconut milk. It must be dried under the sun for at least two hours after being separated from the stalks. According to Bicolanos and Bicolanas, Laing is easy to cook, but it is best cooked if the taro leaves are directly sourced from the Bicol province. In the Philippines, there are various Bicol Laing-inspired food since it is significant in most Bicolano and Bicolana houses. However, in the Metro, Masiram by L’s El Pork Laing is well-known as it promotes the authentic taste of Laing, which certainly originated from the province of  Bicol.
subject: Product Shot
location: 28 Cadig, La Loma, Quezon City, Metro Manila

title: PRODUCT SHOT - EL LAING
creator: Savier Rolan B. Moya
description: Aside from the classic, El Pork Laing, Masiram by L’s prepares and promotes a variety of Laing dishes. One of the main dishes of this online food business is the El Laing Tinapa. Moreover, this kind of Laing still comprises dried taro leaves simmered slowly in thick coconut milk, including tinapa that gives a different and unique taste and makes this cuisine more smoky and savory. These tinapa flakes complement the original taste of Laing, which satisfies the consumers' palate and marks its authenticity. The adding of the red and green chili peppers also serve as the indicator of its spiciness. In fact, these spicy delicacies are indeed Bicol’s trademark when it comes to its various food products. Nevertheless, this variant of Laing is perfect for those people who are not into the pork or chicken kind of Laing.
subject: Product Shot
location: 28 Cadig, La Loma, Quezon City, Metro Manila

title: PRODUCT SHOT - EL PINANGAT
creator: Savier Rolan B. Moya
description: In the Bicol region, there exists the traditional Filipino stew called El Pinangat. This food product is also offered by Masiram by L’s, preparing two of its main variants to deliver its authentic taste. One of the variants is a sour version in which it includes fish, bilimbi, and vinegar. The other variant is known for being prepared by the Bicolanos and Bicolanas with a variety of spices and coconut milk. In fact, Bicol is recognized for its abundant source of taro, but it also has a lot of other ingredients that are commonly utilized in Bicolano and Bicolana cuisine. Nevertheless, the El Pinangat of Masiram by L’s is creamy and usually served with a variety of toppings, which is prevalent and popular because it requires little effort to prepare as long as the combined ingredients are to be cooked together.
subject: Product Shot
location: 28 Cadig, La Loma, Quezon City, Metro Manila
